title: Lesser Antillean swift
text:
The lesser Antillean swift ("Chaetura martinica") is a species of <a href="Swift%20%28bird%29">swift</a> in the family <a href="Apodidae">Apodidae</a>.
It breeds on <a href="Dominica">Dominica</a>, <a href="Guadeloupe">Guadeloupe</a>, <a href="Martinique">Martinique</a>, <a href="Saint%20Lucia">Saint Lucia</a> and <a href="Saint%20Vincent%20%28island%29">Saint Vincent</a>. There is a possible record from <a href="Nevis">Nevis</a>.
Its natural <a href="habitat">habitat</a>s are subtropical or tropical moist lowland <a href="forest">forest</a>s and heavily degraded former forest.
